The Soundscape: The courtyard hums with the layered white noise of a working magical city. The sharp snap-hiss of apprentices practicing warding spells, the heavy, crystalline thud-crunch of Frost Atronachs hauling supplies, and the low, constant, ear-ringing vibration of the city's magical shielding. Beneath it all, inescapable, is the "Pulse"ΓÇöa rhythmic, muffled, metallic THUM... THUM... THUM... echoing up through the paving stones from the sealed Hall of the Elements directly ahead.
The Scent: The air tastes sharply of ozone, burning copper, crushed lavender, and the distinct, sterile smell of heated frost.
II. ARCHITECTURE & KEY LANDMARKS
The ground is paved with seamless, interlocking slabs of pale, blue-veined marble. There are no straight lines; the paths sweep in elegant, organic curves, mimicking the flow of leylines.
