Dominating the exact center of the courtyard is a colossal stone statue of Arch-Mage Shalidor.
Visual: The statue is immense, hovering roughly two feet off its stone pedestal via magnetic/magical levitation, slowly rotating over the course of the day.
The Magicka Wells: Surrounding the base of the statue are three circular, glowing pools of raw, liquid-blue magicka. These wells power the city's exterior wards.
The Hazard: Gazing directly into the unrefined magicka is dangerous for mortal minds. Any player who stares into the wells must make a Guile Save (TN 12). On a failure, they are Staggered for 1 minute, experiencing terrifying, non-linear hallucinations of Aetherius.
3. The Transit Glyphs (The Freight Elevators)
Set flush into the marble floor near the outer edges of the courtyard are massive, glowing geometric sigils.
Function: These are the physical access points to the Market of Sparks built into the scaffolding beneath the courtyard. Stepping onto a glyph and channeling 1 FP activates it, dropping the user safely through a shaft of hard-light to the bazaar below.
The Visual: Cargo and mages are constantly shooting up from below or dropping down in flashes of blue light, creating a highly vertical, bustling atmosphere.
4. The Anomaly Tethers (The Guard Dogs)
The College doesn't use mortal guards inside the walls. Driven deep into the stone around the perimeter are tall, brass pylons inscribed with binding runes.
The Guardians: Leashed to these pylons by chains of crackling, violet lightning are Magic AnomaliesΓÇöfloating, jagged masses of raw, angry energy with a central, burning "eye."
Behavior: They strain against their magical leashes, crackling aggressively and emitting a high-pitched whine when unrecognized guests (the party) approach within 15 feet.
5. The Facades
From the courtyard, the party can see the massive, sealed double doors leading to the Hall of the Elements (Node 5) straight ahead. To the left and right are the ornate, heavy archways leading to the Hall of Attainment (Node 3) and the Hall of Countenance (Node 4).
