"The Dwemer. They built a mind-cage. A Cognitive Soul Gem. They tried to map a soul onto a crystal lattice to achieve immortality. They failed. But the lattice... the Aetherial Matrix... it is perfect. It can hold an infinite charge without breaking."
The Mission:
"Go to Alftand. Deep in the ice. There is a sealed archive there. The Dwemer called it the 'Cognitorium.' Find the Matrix. Bring it to me. And I will forge you a weapon that will not break, no matter how hard you hit the world."

V. THE WARNING
Hjolmar returns to his anvil. The audience is over.
"The Cognitorium is not empty. The Dwemer left their toys behind. Spiders. Spheres. Centurions. They are running on standby power, glitching, dangerous. Do not break the Matrix when you retrieve it. I do not have a replacement."
The party leaves the Singing Glacier. They are healed, the curse is lifted (for now), and they have a destination: Alftand.

We have Hjolmar. We have the Quest. We have the Destination.
Now we need the Dungeon: Alftand & The Cognitorium. This is where they fight the constructs and stumble upon GEAR.

